      "date": "2013-07-29 15:06:08.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: No score\n\nAs far as I can tell the failure has nothing to do with the patch being tested. Starting back in several test 27 subtests there are a lot of debug log entries like:\n\nLustre: lustre-OST0000-osc-ffff88007cf0dc00: Connection to lustre-OST0000 (at 10.10.4.119@tcp) was lost; in progress operations using this service will wait for recovery to complete\nLustre: lustre-OST0000-osc-ffff88007cf0dc00: Connection restored to lustre-OST0000 (at 10.10.4.119@tcp)\n\nI suspect one of these finally hit in such a way as to cause an error to return to user level and trigger a test failure.",
